---
// Triptych altarpiece, painterly repaint with enriched detail.
// Each panel is an abstract, surreal SVG painting, a loose three-part homage to
// Bosch, not a copy. Painting techniques: radial gradients with off-centre light,
// blurred atmosphere haze (feGaussianBlur), radial glow fields, an feTurbulence
// grain overlay for canvas tooth, organic hand-drawn paths and layered
// translucent shapes. Forms are built from several overlapping passes (base fill,
// shade gradient for volume, spark gradient for the light catch) so there is
// light-to-shadow modelling. Only two filters per panel (soft blur, grain), the
// rest is cheap gradient fills, so the page stays light. No animation.
//
// The frame is one connected carved dark-wood altarpiece: equal-width panels
// butt together (gap 0) so half-posts merge into shared posts, base bands form
// one continuous base and the shaped tops flow into one cresting silhouette.
// Each panel's painted scene is clipped to its organic ogee/foliate opening
// (open-r/w/p), and that same path cuts the wood and carries the gild edge, so
// frame and art never mismatch. Sparing gilding: a fine gold inner edge, a base
// line and a crown fleuron; wood dominates. Below 720px the one-piece frame
// resolves into the swipeable carousel where each panel shows its own crown.
//
// Hover/focus/tap emphasis is in place (the fixed frame cannot flex): the
// focused painting (.panel__lift) lifts and brightens while the others dim, all
// on one shared ease. On a first visit each panel turns open like a door: a
// plain carved-wood back face (.panel__door) shows shut, then the panel rotates
// on its hinge to reveal the painting, staggered left to right. The localStorage
// flag is kept; return visits and reduced motion render open with no turn.
//
// Palette is keyed to the two site themes via the data-theme mechanism Layout
// uses. The flip (black) theme is the primary look. Wood stays dark in both;
// the gild and relief lines shift so they read against each base.
---
<section class="triptych" aria-label="Three streams of work">
